<item>
            <title>[LU-19860] Missing mutex_unlock in chlg_obd_get() error path causes deadlock</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19860</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;chlg_obd_get() in lustre/mdc/mdc_changelog.c acquires chlg_registered_dev_lock but fails to release it when ced_obds list is empty, causing a deadlock for any subsequent caller that tries to acquire the same mutex.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; inline struct obd_device* chlg_obd_get(struct chlg_registered_dev *dev)
{
&#160; &#160; &#160; struct obd_device *obd;
  &#160; &#160; mutex_lock(&amp;amp;chlg_registered_dev_lock);
&#160; &#160; &#160; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (list_empty(&amp;amp;dev-&amp;gt;ced_obds))
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; NULL; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// &amp;lt;-- mutex not released
&lt;/span&gt;&#160; &#160; &#160; ...
&#160; &#160; &#160; mutex_unlock(&amp;amp;chlg_registered_dev_lock);
&#160; &#160; &#160; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; obd;
}&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
